s experience.Spanning the years from a period before historical records to the forcible separation of the Kasuga-Kofukuji complex by the Meiji government in 1868, Grapard presents a wealth of little-known material. He includes translations of rare texts and provides new, accessible translations of familiar documents.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 0aBuddhismxRelationsxShinto. 0aShintoxRelationsxBuddhism. 7aRELIGION / Comparative Religion.2bisacsh  abuddhism.  abuddhist temples.  acomparative religious studies.  ajapan.  ajapanese history.  ajapanese religious history.  akamakura period.  akami.  akasuga cult.  akasuga gongen genki e.  akasuga shrine.  akofukuji kasuga multiplex.  akofukuji temple.  amajor world religions.  ameiji government.  apainted handscrolls.  aplace of worship.  apolytheistic belief system.  apre modern japanese religion.  areligion.  areligious rituals.  ashinto shrines.  ashintoism.  ashrine temple complexes.  asiddhartha gautama.  athe buddha.  aworship.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Package Archive Pre-2000z97831106353480 cprintz978052007097440uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/9780520910362?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520910362423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520910362/original  a978-3-11-063534-8  University of California Press Package Archive Pre-2000b2000  aEBA_FAO  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-UCY